      <hr>
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <p>Citation or information about a publication that is based on the use, study, or analysis
                     of the materials described in the record.
      </p>
      <p>Documentation about a file, etc., is recorded in field 556 (Information about
                     Documentation Note).
      </p>
      <p>This field can also be used to record citations to published sources, such as exhibition
                     or collection catalogs, that contain photocopies or reproductions of items.
      </p>
      <p>Note is sometimes displayed or printed with an introductory term that is generated as a
                     display constant.      </p>
      <hr>
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <h4><span class="box">&#9632;</span> INDICATORS
      </h4>
      <div class="indicator"><strong>First Indicator - Display constant controller</strong> <div class="description">Controls the generation of a display constant preceding the note.
            <div class="indicatorvalue"><strong># - Publications</strong> <div class="description">Used to generate the display constant <em>Publications:</em>.
                  <div class="example">
                     <table width="100%">
                        <tr>
                           <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
